      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Superstar pacer LEAP TO FAME (7) is tuning up for his bid for a third Inter Dominion crown next month and has been terrific this season, his highlight wins including the Miracle Mile and The Race in NZ. A wide draw could pose a challenge but he invariably finds a way to win and his record at this circuit and distance is phenomenal. Always hard to tip against him. THE JANITOR NZ (6) has yet to beat LEAP TO FAME in three clashes but has been close to him twice, including in the Miracle Mile in March when beaten a half neck. Draws inside Leap To Fame and that gives him the chance to get one back on the champ. MINOS NZ (4) was back in winning form at this circuit and distance last week. Takes on two of the very best here but does get the barrier draw advantage on them. CHEERSTOLOU (5) has a great strike rate here, winning 10 of 11 attempts. Readied with a nice trial so include him.",
